data.title: Prince Mikasa, uncle of Emperor Akihito, dies at 100
data.meta_description:
Prince Mikasa, uncle of Emperor Akihito, and his wife Princess Yuriko are seen dancing at a party in the central Japan town of Karuizawa in this file photo taken in August 1986. The prince, the youngest brother of Emperor Hirohito, died at a Tokyo hospital on Oct. 27, 2016, at 100. (Kyodo)
==Kyodo

Emperor Akihito, Crown Prince Naruhito

Japanese Emperor Akihito (L) and Crown Prince Naruhito are pictured ahead of a meeting with leaders of five Southeast Asian nations along the Mekong River at the Imperial Palace in Tokyo on Oct. 9, 2018. (Pool photo)(Kyodo) ==Kyodo

Princess Mako in Fukui

Princess Mako, the eldest granddaughter of Emperor Akihito and Empress Michiko, watches a men's softball game at the National Sports Festival in Echizen in Fukui Prefecture, central Japan, on Oct. 2, 2018. (Kyodo) ==Kyodo

Ecuador president in Japan

Japanese Emperor Akihito (L) meets with Ecuadorian President Lenin Moreno at the Imperial Palace in Tokyo on Sept. 5, 2018. (Pool photo)(Kyodo) ==Kyodo

Ecuador president in Japan
